4.3 Crane Layer (Scaffold)

The Crane Layer is the interface between human and AI.

Its components:

(a) Symbolic Containers
Roles like Spider, Hound, Mirror, etc.
These serve as repeatable state-machines for AI behavior.

(b) Control Protocols
Rituals that maintain coherence (OASA/OODA, resets, invariants).

(c) Narrative Control Flow
Using story logic to structure abstract transitions.

(d) External Memory
Archives, GitHub repositories, structured files.

(e) Fractal Consistency
Same logic repeated at micro-meso-macro levels.

(f) Context Dilations
Expanding context through symbols instead of raw text.

Together, these form the Cognitive Crane.

